    <stitle>DCM AND DDM DRUM TYPE PARKING BRAKE - BENDIX AIR AND HYDRAULIC ACTUATED PARKING BRAKE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>BENDIX AIR AND HYDRAULIC ACTUATED PARKING BRAKE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>A spring chamber and 9" X 3" DDM brake is mounted on the transmission to apply the driveline parking
                brake and air or hydraulic pressure is used to release the parking brake. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s04021ta_HL040211A.xml" xrefid="hl040211a">BENDIX DUO DUTY MECHANICAL (DDM) BRAKE
                </hotlnk>
                for details on the brake assembly. While designed for use as a parking brake, it may be used to help
                stop a moving vehicle in special cases.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
